Reasoning: The paper deals with self-organizing programmable matter, which involves the coordination of multiple computational elements. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the movement and coating of objects, which could fall under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The study of the algorithm's runtime and complexity could also place the paper in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of local interactions and the focus on optimization and competitiveness could suggest the paper belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
